```
Proxmox VE - Step-by-Step VM Creation Guide
============================================

1. Access Proxmox VE Web Interface
-----------------------------------
- URL: https://your-proxmox-ip:8006
- Login with root or a user account with sufficient privileges.
- On the left panel, select the Proxmox node (host server).
- Click "Create VM" on the top right corner.

2. General Tab
--------------
- Node: Automatically selected.
- VM ID: Auto-generated or you can set manually.
- Name: Name of the virtual machine (e.g., ubuntu-server).
- Start after created: Optional checkbox to start the VM after creation.

3. OS Tab
---------
- ISO Image: Select the ISO you uploaded to local storage.
- Guest OS Type: Choose from Linux, Windows, or Other.
- Guest OS Version: Choose the appropriate version to optimize virtualization settings.

4. System Tab
-------------
- BIOS:
  - SeaBIOS: For legacy BIOS support.
  - OVMF (UEFI): For modern UEFI systems.
- Machine:
  - i440fx (default)
  - q35 (used for UEFI and passthrough)
- EFI Disk: Required for UEFI. Stores NVRAM (enable if using OVMF).
- Add TPM: Optional, required for Windows 11.
- SCSI Controller: VirtIO SCSI (recommended for best performance).

5. Hard Disk Tab
----------------
- Bus/Device: Choose SCSI, VirtIO Block, or IDE.
- Storage: Choose the target storage (e.g., local-lvm, local).
- Disk Size: Size of the virtual disk in GB (e.g., 32).
- Discard: Enable TRIM support (for SSDs, optional).
- Cache: Default (No Cache) is safest; write-back can improve performance but may risk data loss.

6. CPU Tab
----------
- Sockets: Number of CPU sockets (usually 1).
- Cores: Number of cores (e.g., 2, 4).
- Type: 'host' is best for performance.
- Enable NUMA: Optional (for NUMA-aware apps).
- CPU Limit and CPU Units: Optional fine-tuning settings.

7. Memory Tab
-------------
- Memory (MB): Set the total RAM for the VM (e.g., 4096 for 4GB).
- Ballooning Device: Optional. Allows Proxmox to adjust memory dynamically.

8. Network Tab
--------------
- Bridge: Select a bridge interface (usually vmbr0).
- Model: Choose VirtIO (for performance) or Intel E1000 (for compatibility).
- MAC Address: Auto-generated or enter manually.
- Firewall: Enable if using Proxmox firewall.
- VLAN Tag: Optional (used for VLAN-separated traffic).

9. Confirm Tab
--------------
- Review all the selected configuration options.
- Click "Finish" to create the VM.

After VM Creation
------------------
- VM will appear in the left sidebar.
- Select the VM and go to the "Console" tab.
- Power on the VM and proceed with the operating system installation using the selected ISO.

Optional Post-Creation Configuration
-------------------------------------
- Add additional hardware (e.g., USB, TPM, GPU).
- Configure backups and replication.
- Setup cloud-init if needed for automated VM provisioning.

End of Guide
#################################################################################################################################################
